      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NICALBI (1) raced handy and boxed on well to finish a close third over 1380m at Hobart after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Freshened and back in trip. Drawn to go close. PENINSULA ROSE (5) last appeared a month ago over 1000m at Bairnsdale when she finished fifth. This is her first run for the John Blacker stable. Likely to give a sight fresh. UNA PALOMA BLANCA (8) has been in the money four times including last start on May 17 when third over 1150m at this track. Has a sound record here with three top-three finishes from four starts. Must be included. THERMAL MISS (7) returned from a spell three weeks ago when she was in the firing line on the corner before being beaten 3.5 lengths into sixth over 1200m at Hobart. Strips fitter and can feature in the finish. SPARK OF FIRE (3) is fitter and with the claim can give a sight.",
